annotationA: Angiotensin-converting enzyme; Peptidyl-dipeptidase activity. It is involved in the biological process described with: proteolysis
annotationB: Accessory gland protein 76A is a protein that shows homology to the serpin serine endopeptidase inhibitor family but is predicted to be non-inhibitory. It is produced in the male accessory glands and transferred to females during mating
